osoft exchange in it.  You have to download an app for that which gives you a free month but then requires payment.I wish it had a volume toggle on the side.  Sometimes its difficult to turn the volume down when needed.I miss being able to save books into folders.  I had my old Kindle organized with folders like Science Fiction, History, Military History Etc.  I want to be able to do this again.  AMAZON FIX THIS!Overall, the Fire is great for what it is supposed to be, a media consumption device.  It is not an IPad killer nor was it designed to be.  With it being integrated into Amazon Prime you get yourself a really cool litle device that allows you to read, watch videos, surf the net and play games.  Just what i wanted.  Hopefully Amazon can fix the small issues i brought up but they do not detract from use of the Fire.Help other customers find the most helpful reviews&nbsp;Was this review helpful to you?&nbsp;YesNoReport abuse|PermalinkComment&nbsp;Comment (1)

