 you try to dim to screen, it's still way too bright. After about 15 minutes of using the Kindle Fire reading in the dark, my eyes start to hurt. In normal bright lit room, I was able to read for longer period of time without any eyesore.Video: 4.5/5Most of the videos I watched are from Amazon Prime. Granted you can copy your own movies to the device, but it won't show up in the video tab, and you'll have to access it from the Video Player application. Watching movies on the device was excellent.Audio: 4.5/5The player works... don't expect Bose sound quality, but then again you're not paying Bose price eitherPower: 5/5I was able to get a 7+ hours on the device with normal use watching videos and reading books. Another positive point is that this device uses a standard micro-USB connector for charging and syncing. One less cable and one less proprietary charger to carry...Design: 5/5This is more of a preference. I personally found the simply square design easy and pleasant to use.Warranty/Support: 5/5So I had this device since late November, and today, the USB port quit charging because it looks like the connector on the Fire device was broken. I was preparing for a long phone call with Amazon and being bounced around different country speaking to different people and hoping they were willing to repair it and be without the device for a few weeks. Instead, it took me less than 1 minute to get a live person. And, it took less than two minutes for the rep to authorized a replacement device (which is being sent 2nd day air). Altogether, it took less than 5 minutes to call this in for warranty. Unbelievable service!Help other customers find the most helpful reviews&nbsp;Was this review helpful to you?&nbsp;YesNoReport abuse|PermalinkComment&nbsp;Comments (5)



