5 of 5 people found the following review helpful5.0 out of 5 starsImpressed, does everything I expected for a great price!,November 16, 2011By&nbsp;Reviews on Amazon(US)  -See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?)This review is from:Kindle Fire, Full Color 7" Multi-touch Display, Wi-Fi (Electronics)I am very happy with my purchase -I was in the market for a e-reader with some extra bells and whistles and this fit the bill perfectly.I owned a Kindle, my husband owns an ipad - I did not want nor need an iPad; and understood when purchasing this that it was not a cheaper version of the ipad but an e-reader with additional capabilities, I also understood that it did not have 3G; fine as I have wireless at home and can always find a hot spot when I need one. I owned the original Kindle, loved it, as I love to read but really liked the idea of owning an e-reader that would also allow me to surf the net; watch movies and use apps . I write all this as I have seen a lot of reviews with people complaining and not that the Kindle does not do what it is supposed to do (faulty devices aside) but that it is not the next iPad which it never set out to be...and of course a $500 device is not going to be comparable with a $200 device!I found these very easy to set up and no faults - I actually purchased three as I want my kids to develop a love of reading so I offloaded their DS etc on ebay and bought this. Now I will say that after setting up all three to my Amazon account, I did not find this route to work well for me - fine for my own device but this also gave my kids access to all my books and movies ( if I want access to movies such as the Hangover, I do not want my kids accessing those) so we set up the kids devices under a spare Amazon account we have and can add all the kids books  / movies to that one account, to be accessible on both their devices!Set up was quick - within minutes, and we quickly set about loading a few books, a movie and a few apps. It was an easy process!! The graphics are simply excellent, movies look like, well, movies, like a mini DVD player. Magazines showed up crisp and clear with bright color and are quickly responsive to the touch screen!  Web browsing is fast, pages load quickly and as soon as we switched it on, it picked up our wireless, so adding the passcode was all we needed to do! The kids enjoyed playing their music on this device and from the other room I could hear (rather annoyingly) Katy Perry loud and clear!!I personally really like the fact that this is backlit - the Kindle was great with the book like pages, but quite frankly, as a night reader, I was never a big fan of the little pop up light from the lighted cover, and though the backlight means that this will not be easily used in bright sunlight this is not an issue for me as I was never comofortable with the idea of sitting outdoors with my Kindle device anyway - that is what disposable magazines are for!For me, this met all my expectations - when I travel I want an e-reader that will hold all my books, any movies or music I want while giving me web browsing capabilies so it fill the bill for a great price - I am very impressed, now all I need is a decent cover!!Help other customers find the most helpful reviews&nbsp;Was this review helpful to you?&nbsp;YesNoReport abuse|PermalinkComment&nbsp;Comment

