en.  I wish that it was possible to make sections of the screen larger by dragging it.  The Fire's web browser will do just fine when I need to get online away from home, which is all I need it for.There are a couple of things about the Fire I don't love.  I'd like to have some control of the carousel which displays an image of the apps used and all the books in my Amazon digital library.  And, I wish there was an external volume button.Even though the Fire has gorilla glass, I bought an inexpensive cover splash SIGNATURE Folio Leather Case Cover Fits Amazon Kindle FIRE Tablet with Stand (Black).  The cover serves two purposes - it'll hold the Fire upright for watching videos &amp; it will protect the Fire when I toss it in my purse.  I also purchased splash GLIDER Stylus for iPad 1, iPad 2, iPhone 4 4S, Samsung Galaxy Tab, Samsung Galaxy S II 2, Motorola Xoom, HTC Thunderbolt, EVO 3D, Atrix, Inspire, Droid 2, Fits the Amazon Kindle Fire, All Touchscreen devices (BLACK).  I only bought the Stylus for use with the Fire's virtual keyboard.  But, I find myself using constantly - even when playing games.I think the Fire is terrific!  It certainly exceeds my expectations for a $199 tablet.Help other customers find the most helpful reviews&nbsp;Was this review helpful to you?&nbsp;YesNoReport abuse|PermalinkComment&nbsp;Comment

