ntally powering down. Would another area of the tablet be better, maybe but certainly not a show stopper. I was not really considering this device for email, (I use a small local POP provider at home so rarely recognized) however once I felt comfortable navigating around the Fire, I decided to try to set it up. Easy steps to do it. I did have a problem where I received an error after going through all the steps and hitting finish..it said it could not connect or server connection failed. Wait for it..............a few minutes later I got a little beep and sure enough, all my new email messages from that evening were on my Fire. COOL! Email works perfectly! The whole carousel complaint thing. You can delete the history! so what's the big deal?I bought the leather dual rooCase and it fits perfectly and keeps it well protected. I am SO happy with my Fire. The free 30 day Prime was a bonus and I did a bit more shopping to take advantage of free shipping on some items I was needing for Christmas anyway.So why only 4 stars you say, and not 5? I would like the ability to add storage via a flash drive or SD card, there was an app I was interested in, one of those sleep sound apps, and it said I needed an SD card to run it. Again, just a slight annoyance, but not a show stopper for my overall needs. Most important to me is I would like the ability to read on my Fire via lovely original eInk as it is SO much easier on my eyes. I am not sure this is even possible though due to the different technologies. Being able to change between the three background/font color combos is at least available and does help a lot. Easy fix for me tho, when reading at night after my eyes have had a long tiring day, I use my 2nd Gen Kindle to read and the sync makes it easy to go from one to the other as I need to. Lastly I would think they could have offered a 3G option as they do in the Kindle. Bottom line, I paid $199 and for that price I am perfectly happy and quite delighted with the new Fir