 example the NY Times is too pricey at $20/month.  For $7.99 a month I'll get the Times electronically but for $20 a month I'll look to free content on the web, NY Times headlines, CNN, MSNBC, USA Today etc.....  Amazon, exert a little influence on them, perhaps a special deal for Prime members?  The same goes for Amazon's video service, it needs more current offerings for $1.99, too many are at $3.99.  For that amount, I'll drive to Redbox.  If you want be to buy a lot of content, decrease prices.  You need to price things low enough so that I don't have to think about it.Help other customers find the most helpful reviews&nbsp;Was this review helpful to you?&nbsp;YesNoReport abuse|PermalinkComment&nbsp;Comment (1)

