 size of a normal paper notebook or an average sized paperback. And no guilt over blowing a mortgage payment on an iPad.Battery life is ok, but not great. I haven't quite put it through its paces yet, but I would imagine I could read some books and watch a video on a standard 3 hour flight.So, I definitely love this tablet and recommend it to anyone that wants a solid tablet that doesn't cost a fortune. The integration with Amazon and Amazon Cloud is great as well. Amazon instant videos are free to Prime members (free 1 month Prime trial with Fire). Oh, and if the Fire 2 comes out in the next few months, worst case: I'm out of $139 and have to buy the Fire 2. :)Help other customers find the most helpful reviews&nbsp;Was this review helpful to you?&nbsp;YesNoReport abuse|PermalinkComment&nbsp;Comment

