4 of 4 people found the following review helpful5.0 out of 5 starsI LOVE my Kindle Fire!,January 13, 2012By&nbsp;M. Fletcher(Poultney, VT USA)  -See all my reviews(REAL NAME)&nbsp;&nbsp;Amazon Verified Purchase(What's this?)This review is from:Kindle Fire, Full Color 7" Multi-touch Display, Wi-Fi (Electronics)I have always wanted a Kindle, and when I told my wife this, we were both thinking about getting the basic one. Then the Fire came out and we decided to get each other one for Christmas. I cannot even describe to you how long that wait was between when we got them to the house (November 22nd) and Christmas day! We did not open them before then, so that morning they were a complete surprise. I love, love, love this thing! (and so does she!)I waited to write a review to see if there were any big problems, and there aren't! Battery life is excellent and I can read books with ease on it. I don't know why people complain about reading on this, it works great for me! I have already read 3 entire books and I am part way through 3 others. I have been a big reader all my life, but haven't felt like I have had the time lately, and didn't want to lug books back and forth to work with me. The Fire makes it so easy! And I also don't have to answer any annoying questions from nosy people who used to see me carrying books and say "what book are you reading?". I bought a cover for it, and I am glad I did. It is always protected.I love that I can play games on it, surf the web, watch Netflix and other movies, email, keep notes, etc, etc, etc! I love that it holds my place in a book and also lets me know what percentage of the book I have read. You can make notes on pages, but I haven't tried that feature yet. I can't put this device down!! It is everything they said it was going to be and more!! I haven't even cracked the surface of all it can do. I learn more about it everyday!I HIGHLY recommend getting a Kindle Fire!!People have complained about the following:1) The power button. I don't know if it's because I have a case for it, but I have never had a problem with accidentally hitting the power off. First of all, you need to hold it in when you want to turn it off, and then press shut down on the screen when it asks you. So I don't know why people have a problem with this. You can put it to sleep by pushing the button once, but this is easily remedied by pressing it again to turn it back on.2) The volume. If you want a device strictly for music, get an IPod. The volume and speakers work just fine for the average person. To find the volume adjuster, tap the arrow at the bottom of the screen and then tap the settings cog next to the wireless indicator and voila! The volume adjuster is right there! (It sounds more cumbersome than it is). You can also see the percentage of battery life left, how much space you've used, and so much more! There is a headphone port and believe me when I say the volume works awesome!3) The keyboard. I guess if your fingers are really fat, you probably won't like the little pop up keyboard. It works fine for me, but of course a touch keyboard will not be as easy to use as an external one.4) The pre-registration and inability to lock. You CAN lock your device. There is a button for it in the settings. If someone hacks that, or if it isn't locked and you leave it lying around or let someone play with it, sure, they can order stuff. I don't know anyone I would let touch it that would seriously order something on my device without asking first. If they do accidentally order something, there is a button to cancel the order.I guess I am not really generous with my electronics. I don't just give them to people to play with, and I always make sure I know where it is. Just warn whomever you let play with it that they shouldn't buy anything with it! And know where it is!If those four things look like something you would have a problem with, don't buy it. If you are an electronics snob who will look for any excuse to complain, don't buy it! If you are someone who enjoys electronics and want a fun and entertaining product, order it NOW!Help other customers find the most helpful reviews&nbsp;Was this review helpful to you?&nbsp;YesNoReport abuse|PermalinkComment&nbsp;Comment

