6 of 7 people found the following review helpful5.0 out of 5 starsThe Fire is as advertised,November 21, 2011By&nbsp;G. McNeil(Spokane, WA)  -See all my reviews(REAL NAME)&nbsp;&nbsp;Amazon Verified Purchase(What's this?)This review is from:Kindle Fire, Full Color 7" Multi-touch Display, Wi-Fi (Electronics)First, let me say I am new to the "tablet" world.  I have looked at quite a few, and decided on the Fire mainly because of Amazon (and the price).  I have been a customer for many years and this device fits my needs.  I was looking for something that would allow internet access, e-mail serivces, and a few games to pass the time on long trips.  The e-book portion was not a consideration at first, but I am impressed.  Having no experience with other e-readers I cannot evaluate how it compares.  I will say I have read 3 books on it so far, and I am hooked.  I had no eye strain or any problems with the unit.The setup was quick and painless.  It took me a while to adjust to the touch screen, and getting around, but feel like a pro at this point.  I also have an old style cellphone so this is my first experience with a touch screen as well. Once I slowed down and became a little careful with my touch, it works fine.  The only time I have issues now is when touching the screen by accident.PROS:FAST INTERNETon my home system.  A little slower but managable on other networks.  Starbucks was the worst I have found so far, but it was usable.EXCELLENT SCREEN FOR movies, videos, etc.  I am very impressed with it.  I can tell right away I will need a car charger for it, as my lovely bride has already ordered a few movies to download.A GOOD READABLE SCREEN FOR BOOKS -  I adjusted the font and background to my liking, and I can imagine many hours spent reading.  I am plesently suprised how much I like this feature.  Others have commented it does not reach the level of the current e-readers, but for me, it is perfect.IT HAS MORE APPS THAN I WILL EVER USE/NEED.  The free app every day is a cheap way to start learning what is out there.  Since this is new territory, I guess I do not know what I am missing, but there is more now than I will ever use (OK - never say never).GOOD E-MAIL SERVICE.  Another reviewer complained it does not delete mail on the server.  Go to options/fetchmail and you can set it up any way you want.  I like the way it works.  Fits my needs exactly.STREAMING VIDEO - Was not a selling point for me, but now it is.  I love it.  G3 would have been nice, but I knew going in it required a wireless connection to function.  Except when in a car, I have wireless available most places I go, so it is not an issue.  Still, G3....CONS:A LITTLE HEAVIER than I thought (I know, I know-the weight was clearly stated, but still, I'm sayin...).  It is by no means too heavy, and I have already adjusted to the weight, and don't notice it now.THE CAROUSEL - Amazon needs to fix it so I can delete or hide what shows and what does not.  I want it be be functional and usable - I like the idea of it, showing me the last few usages, but even in my short time with it, it is becoming huge with stuff I looked at, decided against, and deleted.  The stuff never goes away (so far).ONE-CLICK - Well, not an issue with me but I understand the concerns others have mentioned with no way to lock it out or require a password.  I understand that means it is no longer one-click, but the option should be there.  Also, protection when going into settings.  I could turn off wireless if a password was required to turn it back on when my granddaughter is playing with it, as I am sure she will.MEH???THE CLOUD - not sure if I am a fan or not.  It works as advertised so far.  I have no problem with storing my stuff there and downloading when I need/want it.  Just too new for me to decide about it.  I think more memory or an SD card would be nice, but so far its not an issue with me.  In fact, I still have over 6 gigs available.  I know the first movie or two will take a huge bite, but watch it, delete it from the unit and go get another, knowing it can be downloaded again whenever I want.  Given the memory restrictions, the cloud might be the answer.  Time will tell.TOUCHSCREEN -  I would like to see a means to adjust the sensitivity.  Also, sometimes it is very touchy and sometimes my hand brushs past the unit causing it to respond.  Probably user error.  Again, time will tell.  I am already better than day one.Overall, I am impressed and very happy with the unit.  I would recomend it to anyone provided they understand what it does and does not do.Help other customers find the most helpful reviews&nbsp;Was this review helpful to you?&nbsp;YesNoReport abuse|PermalinkComment&nbsp;Comment

