3 of 3 people found the following review helpful5.0 out of 5 starsBest Device I Own!,February 27, 2012By&nbsp;H. Potter "Oldhiker"(California)  -See all my reviews(REAL NAME)&nbsp;&nbsp;Amazon Verified Purchase(What's this?)This review is from:Kindle Fire, Full Color 7" Multi-touch Display, Wi-Fi (Electronics)According to media reviews, the Fire was not supposed to be as good an e-reader as the E-Ink Kindles, of which I have two. Not so. It is a superb e-reader, unless you sit in direct sun all the time. For indoor lighting, the bright screen is perfect; it looks much more like a paper book than the old gray and white, and you don't need to shine a bright light on it. There are also more choices in typefaces, brightness, margins, and overall appearance. And the screen image automatically changes if you switch from portrait to landscape format and back.It is great for Web browsing, too. Its speed is terrific, sometimes faster than the high speed cable attached to my desktop. The screen is sharp and videos are very crisp. But wireless use drains the battery very rapidly. It probably wouldn't last much more than two hours if you were downloading content all the time. I wouldn't seriously consider using the Fire to watch TV or movies. But then, books are better entertainment, anyway.The only trouble I had with it was learning how to work the touchscreen surface; I was pressing too hard. It takes a very gentle touch. It responds to the same pressure as my IPod Classic (sorry Amazon, I won't be downloading music to my Fire).The only criticism that seems justified is the one about the power button. It is right in the middle of the bottom and it is really easy to turn the thing off by accident, especially if you lie on your back and rest the Fire on your chest. So I turn it to landscape orientation to avoid the problem.  A sliding switch, as the older Kindles have, would be a better solution.Help other customers find the most helpful reviews&nbsp;Was this review helpful to you?&nbsp;YesNoReport abuse|PermalinkComment&nbsp;Comment

