3 of 3 people found the following review helpful5.0 out of 5 starsThe Kindle is on Fire!!!,January 20, 2012By&nbsp;HD Eyes-See all my reviewsThis review is from:Kindle Fire, Full Color 7" Multi-touch Display, Wi-Fi (Electronics)First of all, I have the older kindle for reading and love it. When I saw the Kindle Fire came out...I knew I had to have it. I receieved it as my christmas present this year, and I love it. It is so much more than I ever imagined it would be. I love playing time management games on the WII, and was so pleased that the kindle had many games to play. The only  drawback is that I can't put it down and I am constantly playing games. The picture is crisp and clear, and the colors are very vibrant. Having only one computer in my house, I love going online with my kindle fire. It is simple and easy to use and had no problems moving around the web. I placed my favorite songs in there, and I love Amazon Cloud which connects my music from my kindle, to computer- very easy to use. The movies and videos are crisp and clear. There are two speakers so the sound is above average, but for even better sound just plug in your headphones and you are good to go. The battery life isn't bad at all. Depending on how much time you spend on it I can see charging the battery nightly. I usually have to do every other night. Just plug it in when you go to bed, and when you wake it ready to go. Now here is the only problem I found with the kindle fire- however, I have fixed that problem. When I started reading books I realized that I was getting headaches. The light was just so bright and no matter how much I lowered it...it was still too bright. I was devestated. Just when I was about to give up and leave the reading for my other kindle, I decided to go on the web and find some help. The first thing I found was that people said to switch the white background to black and letters from black to white. IT WORKED!! I was happy and no more headaches. So, I was reading like that for a while, but it still felt off because it wasn't like a book. I went on the web again and read this. Someone said to go and download a screen filter. I couldn't find it, but luckily my brother did and put it in my kindle. What it does is let you lower the light even more than kindle allows, and it works. I don't know exactly how to get that screen filter, but if you search the web you will find it there. So now when I read my book I click on the screen filter icon and the whole kindle goes dark. Then I adjust the brightness in my settings up to a nice soft glow. Also I set my background color to the sepitone(don't know if spelt right) color. I felt it was more like a book than plain white. Thank God I solved this problem and now reading if perfect. If you have any questions feel free to contact me. I know how disappointed I was until I found the solution. Now I love my kindle. The only thing missing is a camera. It is a little on the heavy, but not bad. I am sure when they make a two, it will be slimmer and include a camera. So now the only disappointment was that it did not come with a USB cord. So if you wanted to transfer things from your computer to your kindle or vice versa, you would have to go out and buy a USB chord. Luckiy I have the origina Kinde which comes with a USB chord, and so I can use that. All in all, I Love it. Its the perfect size to carry around and is there if I want to watch a movie, go on the web, play music, play games or just read a book or magazine for that matter. It is well worth the price when comparing it to the apple I pad. Kindle is my friend.Help other customers find the most helpful reviews&nbsp;Was this review helpful to you?&nbsp;YesNoReport abuse|PermalinkComment&nbsp;Comment (1)

