3 of 3 people found the following review helpful4.0 out of 5 starsJust what I needed.,December 21, 2011By&nbsp;MsButter-See all my reviewsThis review is from:Kindle Fire, Full Color 7" Multi-touch Display, Wi-Fi (Electronics)When purchasing new products, I read the worst reviews first, then make my decision based on whether or not I'm willing to take the risk.  In the case of the Fire, it was a gift, and one I am most definitely pleased with.I find none of the problems I read about in other reviews.  For example, one of the most concerning was password protection.  The fire is perfectly cable of being password protected.  It was the very first feature I found and activated and it works wonderfully.  I have to enter my password every time I use my Fire, even if only for the briefest of moments.Another common complaint was that you couldn't read all your books on the fire.  I also found this to be untrue.  There is some difficulty associated with getting certain titles to show on the fire, but it is not impossible.  In fact, this extra step is why I knocked my rating down to four stars.  Here is what I found, for titles that do not show up on your Fire, simply connect your Kindle USB cord directly to your computer, go to Your Account, Manage Your Kindle, and Download via USB.  If you follow the transfer tip that appears in gray, the selection will immediately appear on the bookshelf of your Fire.All in all, the only other complaint that I have about the fire is simply the choice of charging adapter.  I prefer the USB charger that comes with the other model Kindle's over what the Fire comes with (the old plug me into the wall kind, thankfully I have a regular outlet in my truck or long drives would suck), it makes life a lot simpler to be able to have a universal source.  Thankfully, everyone in my household has their own Kindle, so we have plenty to go around.This is an excellent device.  I wouldn't trade it for any other in the world right now.  If you are considering this but are concerned about some of the negative reviews like I was, there is also one other thing to consider.  The Kindle Fire (and everything else Amazon.com) is guaranteed, so if you don't like it, just print the return label and send it back.We Want It AllHelp other customers find the most helpful reviews&nbsp;Was this review helpful to you?&nbsp;YesNoReport abuse|PermalinkComment&nbsp;Comment

