3 of 3 people found the following review helpful4.0 out of 5 starsGreat tablet for the price,December 13, 2011By&nbsp;P. A. Sugg(Memphis,TN)  -See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?)This review is from:Kindle Fire, Full Color 7" Multi-touch Display, Wi-Fi (Electronics)I have had my fire for about a month now, and while it took some getting used to, I have to say I am really enjoying it. I use it primarily for reading books and watching videos that I have purchased through Amazon. I use some of the Android apps, and surf the internet occasionally.I was worried that reading on a backlit screen would be difficult on my eyes, but I can adjust the brightness to a level that does not cause any discomfort. However, I also do not read for more than an hour or so at a time. I have many e-book titles and this is one of the main reasons I got the fire.I purchase many tv shows and rent most of my movies from Amazon. I love that I can purchase them through my blu-ray player or my fire and through the cloud, I can watch them on either device, and even my pc. I can also download purchased movies or shows to my fire and watch them when I travel.I have found that not having 3G is not an issue for me because I can download the entertainment that I need and if I have to pull a website I can just use my iphone. As far as the speed for loading web pages, there are times when it takes longer to load pages, but it really isnt that noticeable. I don't think it is any slower than my iphone 4.Not having an external volume control can be annoying. But, once I get it to the level I need, I don't have to continually adjust it, so it isn't that bad. I have also noticed that the touch screen does have some delay at times. When I touch a link from a Google search, sometimes it takes several taps for it to recognize it. And I do not have fat fingers..You will have to view web pages on the horizontal view. And, you will have to zoom in to many of the web pages you are viewing. This can get annoying as well, but you should expect that with a 7" screen. It is also somewhat difficult to move between applications. I am used to being able to swtich back and forth between apps very easily with my iphone, so it has taken some getting used to.I have seen some complaints about the privacy with regards to the history of the content you have recently viewed. For example, If I pull my bank info, once I close out of the page, the last screen shot will appear on my home page's history for anyone who picks up the kindle after me to see. However, if you clear your web history, the pages will not show up on the home screen. It is a bit of a hassle, but it's a limitation you can get around.For $200 this is an incredible tablet. I use it daily and I am very pleased with it. I rated it a 4 star because there are some limitations that I believe could be addressed. If you are an Amamzon prime member, which I am not, this is really a must have device. You have access to many more videos and tv shows for no extra charge, as well as a great book lending service. If you use Amazon regularly, which I do, then I would highly recommend this tablet. It is not better than an iPad by any means, but for $200, it is a great device.Help other customers find the most helpful reviews&nbsp;Was this review helpful to you?&nbsp;YesNoReport abuse|PermalinkComment&nbsp;Comment

