3 of 3 people found the following review helpful5.0 out of 5 starsGreat device but needs STRONG wifi connection for some functions,December 11, 2011By&nbsp;Luv2BikeColorado(Denver)  -See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?)This review is from:Kindle Fire, Full Color 7" Multi-touch Display, Wi-Fi (Electronics)I am thrilled with my Fire but like many reviewers before me, I initially had LOTS of trouble with my wifi connection.  I spent the first few weeks borrowing a signal from a few nearby unsecured weak (2 bars) wifi signals.  The Fire would repeatedly disconnect and re-connect.  I could not stay connected to the internet, download a book, or watch video without frequent interruptions due to a dropped signal.  Finally, I installed my own wi-fi in my residence.  My connection is now full strength (4 bars) and I no longer have any connectivity problems!!  Please note that even a "fair" 2-bar signal would not hold a connection on my Fire.  A STRONG wi-fi connection might be what's needed to eliminate connectivity problems.  For some reason, the Kindle won't run right off a weaker signal, while my next-door neighbor's laptop works fine with a 2-bar signal.  Perhaps Amazon, in trying to make this device affordable, installed a lower-quality wifi device on the Fire.  One solution to this problem would be to buy a USB wifi booster....but the Fire has no USB port.  This may be a problem we Fire owners are going to be stuck with, until an improved version of the Fire comes out.  This is probably a hardware issue that cannot be solved by an over-the-air update.Help other customers find the most helpful reviews&nbsp;Was this review helpful to you?&nbsp;YesNoReport abuse|PermalinkComment&nbsp;Comment

