3 of 3 people found the following review helpful4.0 out of 5 starsAlmost Perfect,November 16, 2011By&nbsp;P. C. Jackson "Abba's Girl"-See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?)This review is from:Kindle Fire, Full Color 7" Multi-touch Display, Wi-Fi (Electronics)I got mine earlier today (am writing on it now) and have spent several hours trying out all the different features. Here's my opinion:The Kindle is very solid; in fact almost too heavy to hold for any significant amount of time. I definitely need to purchase a case with a built-in stand. The screen is a very thick strong glass which cleans easily with a soft cloth. The images are crisp, bright and very clear.  I have the brightness set to midway and it is bright enough; any more would be too bright for me. All my Kindle books were automatically displayed in the carousel and there are hundreds of books that I have purchased from Amazon over the years... these are ALL displayed in the carousel. It would be nice to have more control of the carousel though.I played some music--sounds great but you really need to attach headphones or external speakers to hear it loud enough in my opinion. I watched a little bit of a movie which I downloaded for free as a Prime member and the video is extraordinary; beautiful rich colors and sharp images. But again, you really need to have external speakers or headphones to hear the sound better. My one disappointment in this area is that is has no bluetooth capabibilityReading books on the Fire is easy and very good. I do find it more comfortable on my eyes if I either change the color of the background to black with white text or if you use the black text on a white background then dim the brightness way down. I have found that this works well for me as well when I read on my iPad.I had lots of apps to choose from and downloaded a number of them which work well so far.I saved my review of the web browser for last because that is what I least like about the Kindle Fire. It quit on me a couple of times and I found it to lag somewhat. It is not as responsive as the iPad browser and needs some work on it to be optimally useful.The battery does not last 7-8 hours as advertised. I had to charge it after a few hours of use. Maybe it would get that much time if you disable the wifi and just read a book. I don't know what the life of the battery is and I know that it has to be replaced by Amazon so be prepared to use the AC adapter often. I hope I can find a car charger for it as well.All in all, I am quite pleased with it. However, I can tell that Amazon needs to make some improvements for future Kindles. It is not as superb as the iPad but it is a nifty toy to play with. I think I will mainly be using it for reading and watching free movies from Amazon. I won't be using the web browser because it is too buggy and the screen is just too small for reading web material.So that's my opinion for what it's worth. I hope this was helpful for someone. Now back playing with my new toy for awhile...Help other customers find the most helpful reviews&nbsp;Was this review helpful to you?&nbsp;YesNoReport abuse|PermalinkComment&nbsp;Comment (1)

