}Length:: 7:55 MinsCompared Kindle Fire with Lenovo A1(7"), Dell Streak (7") and Velocity Cruz (8") in my video review.* While Kindle lacks certain features such as Camera &amp; GPS - Kindle fire comes with the best quality display and touch screen* It is an extremely frustrating experience to use touch screen on the other tablets - yes it may have some nice features, but no point if you start pulling your hair to get the touch screen work the way you think.* If you are looking for a fully featured tablet - Dell Streak 7" is the best one out there.  But if you are looking for a top quality tablet for under $200 - look no further - Kindle Fire is the best.* Android Market does not ship with Kindle Fire and yes we really miss out on a lot of some really cool apps. But there is a downside to it i.e proliferation of spamware and malware.  Getting your Apps through the Amazon Appstore assures you a peace of mind that it does not contain any viruses and malware.Hopefully the Amazon AppStore will start carrying a lot more apps for Kindle Fire in the coming few months.Help other customers find the most helpful reviews&nbsp;Was this review helpful to you?&nbsp;YesNoReport abuse|PermalinkComment&nbsp;Comment

