5 of 6 people found the following review helpful5.0 out of 5 starsA Super Satisfied Customer,December 16, 2011By&nbsp;cicsos2 "Bill"(Texas)  -See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?)This review is from:Kindle Fire, Full Color 7" Multi-touch Display, Wi-Fi (Electronics)I started in the eReader world with a Kindle 2.  When the Kindle with WiFi came out, I got one and gave my K2 to my grandson. I love to read and have been since my grade school days.  I have kept more books than I have resold.  When I found out about the Gutenberg books being available for the Kindle I was really happy.  Over 60% of the books on my K3 were from one of the free ebooks sites (these are legitimate sites).  I found books that I can remember reading as a young person and I got these and read them once again.I used my K2 and K3 readers a lot, one of the benefits of retirement.  During the year where I took my K3 everywhere with an unlighted cover, no less, I had it reboot only two or three times.  I finally did upgrade to a lighted cover.  I have had zero WiFi problems, no matter where I went.  The keys look as good as new.My personal background includes software development &amp; testing plus writing manuals for software. (I go back to punch card days)All of this background is to show that I had high expectations for the Kindle Fire. By the way, my wife has an iPad(1) with 3G that she really likes.  On rare occasions she will let me borrow it for a few minutes.  I also have to do the iTunes maintenance for both her iPhone and iPad ... and I have learned to really dislike iTunes!There is a term that has been used in some areas called "the out of the box experience" - or how hard or easy is it to get a product into productive use.  I would rate the Kindle Fire as one of the very best for an "out of the box experience".  Just for fun, I made pictures of each tiny step, from opening the box to having the Fire ready to read a book.  Even with taking pictures it went very smoothly.  The hardest step was entering the fairly long security code for the wireless router. I did have to wait a minute or so for the V6.1 upgrade to complete before I could start playing with this beautiful device.I also bought one of the simple Marware plastic cases - and have no regrets with that decision.  It does a good job protecting the screen and the power button.  I do keep a microfiber towel handy for wiping the fingerprints (and I gave my wife her own towel for her iPad).To be fair, there are some areas where the product could be improved - but that is nothing new (I assume that you, the reader of this review, do understand that there have been many more software releases than eight for the Microsoft Windows Operating System - that's the nature of the game).For example, there needs to be more user control over the book covers shown in the carousel or perhaps the ability to clear the contents.  We need to ability to download Personal Documents, pictures, etc directly from the cloud, just like as can be done with Books.  We need the ability to easily uninstall applications and, perhaps, that ability to extend the 1G area reserved for applications.In summary, I would not hesitate to buy one of these devices as long as you understand it's target audience.Help other customers find the most helpful reviews&nbsp;Was this review helpful to you?&nbsp;YesNoReport abuse|PermalinkComment&nbsp;Comment



